Class UndoableObjects

  • java.lang.Object
    • datastructures.UndoableObjects
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class UndoableObjects
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Database of objects, for which Undo and Redo operations are made possible. The algorithm works only for objects containing no references.
    Version:
    $Id: $Id
    Author:
    Alfons Wirtz

      • undo

        public boolean undo(java.util.Collection<UndoableObjects.Storable> p_cancelled_objects,
                    java.util.Collection<UndoableObjects.Storable> p_restored_objects)
        Restores the situation before the last snapshot. Outputs the cancelled and the restored objects (if != null) to enable the calling function to take additional actions needed for these objects. Returns false, if no more undo is possible
        Parameters:
        p_cancelled_objects - a Collection object.
        p_restored_objects - a Collection object.
        Returns:
        a boolean.

        public boolean redo(java.util.Collection<UndoableObjects.Storable> p_cancelled_objects,

        Parameters:

        p_restored_objects - a Collection object.
        Returns:
        a boolean.

      • pop_snapshot

        public boolean pop_snapshot()
        Removes the top snapshot from the undo stack, so that its situation cannot be restored any more. Returns false, if no more snapshot could be popped.
        Returns:
        a boolean.
